  {
    "content_id": 133001,
    "reference_id": 109055,
    "title": "1 Peter 5:1–5",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "60005001-60005005",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Peter described <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108118\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">church elders</span> and leaders as <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108278\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">shepherds</span> over God’s people.</p><p>His instructions to them were like Jesus’ instructions to his <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108040\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">disciples</span> in Luke 22:24–30.</p><p>Church leaders mustn’t act proud or act like rulers. Jesus is the Chief Shepherd and they must obey him.</p><p>They must follow Jesus’ example of being a <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108059\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">leader who served</span>.</p><p>Leaders who serve faithfully will share Jesus’ glory when he returns to earth.</p><p>Other believers must respect and follow leaders who lead like Jesus.</p>",
