  {
    "content_id": 133002,
    "reference_id": 109056,
    "title": "1 Peter 5:6–14",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "60005006-60005014",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Peter ended his letter by encouraging the believers in several ways. He reminded them that God truly cares about his people. They can trust God completely.</p><p>The devil tries to make believers doubt God and stop obeying him. Peter described this like the devil swallowing them up. But God gives believers the grace they need to oppose the devil. They are humble but God is mighty. He gives them strength to hold on to what they believe.</p><p>Believers aren’t alone as they struggle and suffer. God’s people all over the world are also suffering and are struggling against evil. They are joined together as one in <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108045\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">God’s family</span> and in friendship.</p><p>Greetings from <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108121\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">Silas</span>, <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108069\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">Mark</span> and the church also encouraged the believers. Peter used the name <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108498\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">Babylon</span> to talk about Rome.</p>",
